## Version Numbering Examples

### Development Phase
- `0.1.0` - Initial development
- `0.2.0` - Added authentication
- `0.3.0` - Added budget features
- `0.9.0` - Pre-release candidate

### Production Releases
- `1.0.0` - First stable release (MVP complete)
- `1.0.1` - Bug fix release
- `1.1.0` - New feature (receipt photos)
- `1.2.0` - More features
- `2.0.0` - Major rewrite or breaking changes

---

## Best Practices

### ✅ DO
- Bump version for every user-facing change
- Use semantic versioning consistently
- Tag every version
- Push tags immediately after creating them
- Update release notes for significant changes
- Commit frequently with descriptive messages

### ❌ DON'T
- Skip version bumps for "small" changes (users notice!)
- Create tags without pushing them
- Bump major version for minor changes
- Forget to update multiple version locations
- Commit without descriptive messages

